    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to the work of a group of artists exhibiting in New York in the mid-1980s. Incorporating ideas from earlier movements such as Dada, Hard-Edge, and Pop, the work is purposefully calculating and intellectual and includes paintings in flat, Dayglo colors, kitsch objects, and sculpture made out of consumer products.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Se refiere al trabajo de un grupo de artistas que exhiben en el Pueblo del Este de Nueva York a mediados de los años 80. Incorporando ideas de los movimientos precedentes como Dada, Hard-edge y Pop Art, la composición es determinadamente calculada e intelectual e incluye pinturas en colores planos, Dayglo, objetos kitch y escultura elaborada con productos de consumo.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Verwijst naar het werk van een groep kunstenaars die hun werk in het midden van de jaren 80 van de 20ste eeuw tentoonstelde in de New Yorkse wijk East Village. De groep gebruikte de ideeën van eerdere stromingen zoals Dada, ‘Hard-Edge’ en Pop art in werk dat doelbewust berekenend en rationeel is, bijvoorbeeld in schilderijen in harde neonkleuren, kitschobjecten en beeldhouwwerken vervaardigd van consumentenproducten.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052378/Winkler Prins Encyclopedie (1990)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>指於80年代中期，在紐約展覽的藝術家團體之作品。創作靈感融合早期的藝術運動如達達（Dada）、硬邊藝術（Hard-Edge）及普普藝術（Pop）等，試圖創作經過審慎計算且充滿知性的作品，其中包括以呆板的幻彩螢光漆（Dayglo）繪畫、媚俗物件以及由消費產品製作而成的雕塑。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refere-se ao trabalho de um grupo de artistas que expôs em Nova York em meados da década de 1980. Incorporando ideias de movimentos anteriores, como Dada, Hard-Edge e Pop, o trabalho é propositalmente calculista e intelectual e inclui pinturas planas, cores Dayglo, objetos kitsch e esculturas feitas de produtos de consumo.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Portuguese</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
